  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CPB device operates in clinical environments subject to temperature drift (patient warming/cooling circuits, OR ambient swings 18–26°C), ambient pressure variation (altitude-dependent installations, 700–101 kPa), and electromagnetic interference from electrosurgical units and imaging equipment. Validation activities were conducted exclusively under controlled laboratory conditions at 22°C and atmospheric pressure; no environmental-sensitivity study characterising the effect of these operating-envelope variations on CFD hemolysis predictions has been performed or linked.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
