      "rationale": "Five flow-speed combinations spanning CPB clinical range tested in vitro. Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, 40% haematocrit equivalent viscosity) used at 22°C. Fluid density and viscosity measured at test temperature. Temperature was controlled at 22°C throughout; the clinical temperature range (33–38°C patient, 18–26°C OR ambient) was not replicated. Ambient pressure held at 101.3 kPa; altitude-dependent pressure variation not explored. No EMI sources were present during testing. These environmental conditions are representative of the laboratory but do not bound the full clinical deployment envelope."
