      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating conditions match COU device geometry and intended operating range.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used for both validation and COU prediction. Operating flow-speed combinations overlap with clinical CPB range. Validation activities are considered relevant to the COU for the purposes of hemolysis index prediction under standard laboratory conditions. Environmental operating parameters of the clinical deployment environment (temperature drift, ambient pressure at altitude, EMI from electrosurgical equipment) are outside the scope of the validation activities as conducted; this scope limitation is noted but not assessed as a separate credibility factor at MRL 2."
